 two nations that has changed the image of Japan in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCultural fusion. 4aAmerica. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aAsia. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCulture. 4aJapan. 4aMedia. 4aUSA. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican Studies.  aAsia.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aJapan.  aMedia.  aUSA.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066155208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Lit. & Kultur 2010-2013z978311037074408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839426005zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839426005423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839426005/original  a978-3-11-037074-4  transcript Highlight Collection Lit. & Kultur 2010-2013c2010d2013  a978-3-11-066155-2  transcript English Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TGPb2013  aZDB-23-TSOc2010d2013